### Could Zustand store transitions create unbounded re-render chains?

No. The `parameterPointsProgram` state machine is strictly `IDLE -> LOADING -> SUCCESS|ERROR`. The guard clause in the service (`if status === LOADING || SUCCESS, return`) ensures idempotency. Even if a re-render were to somehow re-trigger the service, the guard would prevent any state mutation, breaking the cycle.

The `useShallow` selectors on the other two slices (`pointsProducts`, `pointsBalance`) are read-only in this screen -- no effect or callback in `InvoiceCashbackPoints` triggers mutations to those slices. They can only change from external actions (other screens or background processes), which would cause a re-render but would NOT re-trigger any effect (all effects have stable deps).

